	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 729" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2697> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2697" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 43.11.13. On Flamininus, see Lübker no. 12." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2696> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2696" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The name of the successor to Flamininus lost in a lacuna in the text of Livy." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2193> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2193" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed as a Legate under Glabrio by the Senate (Liv. 36.1.8)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2148> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2148" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the doubts regarding Furius' achievements in the same area both as Pr. and as Cos., see 200, Praetors, and Münzer, RE." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2147> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2147" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Polyb. 21.32.13; Liv. 35.10.10; 38.11.9; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 121, 454f.; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Flamininus, CIL 1\n     .2.613- ILS 14; Cic. Sen. 42; Val. Max. 4.5.1. Flamininus was assigned Italy, Gaul, and the holding of the elections (Liv. 35.20.1-7, and 20.4-6), and Domitius a province outside of Italy in case of war with Antiochus (35.20.7), but otherwise Italy and the Gauls (35.20.2). Both were actively engaged in Italy, Flamininus against the Ligurians and Domitius against the Boii (35.22.3-4, and 40.2-4). On Flamininus, see Lübker no. 12." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2108> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2108" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Continued with Flamininus in Greece as a Legate in charge of the fleet (Liv. 34.50.11; see 198-195). See Lübker, no. 12." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2088> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2088" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Continued in command of the fleet (Liv. 34.26.11; 34.29-30, and 40.7; cf. Zon. 9.18). See Lübker no. 12." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2023> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2023" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legate under his brother and in command of the fleet; see 198, and esp. Liv. 33.17.2. On his operations, see Liv. 33.16-17. See Lübker, no. 12." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2007> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2007" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legate (Liv. 33.17.2 and 15). The Senate gave him charge of the fleet in Greece and command of the coast (Liv. 32.16.2). On his campaign, see Liv. 32.16-17, 19-23, 39-40; CIL 1\n     .2.613- ILS 14. See Lübker, no. 12." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2006> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2006" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The phrases describing Flamininus' command, \"cui classis cura maritimaeque orae imperium mandatum ab senatu erat\" (Liv. 32.16.2) in 198, and \"praeesse eidem quae praeerat classi iussus\" (32.28.9) in 197, and the fact that he had just been Pr. Urbanus, all suggest that his imperium as Praetor was prorogued. But he is definitely termed a Legatus (Liv. 33.17.2 and 15). Note that in 193 Ti. Sempronius Longus (Cos. 194) is termed a Legatus of Merula in Gaul (35.5.1), but in contrast with the other Legatus Marcellus (Cos. 196) is referred to later as possessing imperium (35.8.6). See Mommsen, Str. 2.675-701, esp. 683; and on Flamininus, Jashemski, op. cit. (see 205, note 2) 28." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1962> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1962" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See Lübker, no. 12." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1961> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1961" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "L. Flamininus may have performed the duties of both Pr. Urbanus and Peregrinus; cf. Mommsen, Str. 2.210, note 5." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1905> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1905" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 31.4.5-6. On Quinctius, see Lübker, no. 12; on Valerius, Münzer, Gent. Val. 39, no. 17." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1510> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1510" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "L. Quinctius Flamininus succeeded P. Furius Philus. Liv. 25.2.2; see 214, Censors." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1509> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1509" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "L. Flamininus, brother of Titus Flamininus, the liberator of the Greeks, would have been very young at this time, but it seems improbable that no close relative of his should have held a major priesthood (Münzer, APF 118f.; Bardt 18f.)." .
